imally adjust two problematic cases regarding color assertions. For the reset with true background, I shouldn’t assert that it gets the exact `getColor D`. Instead, it would be better to assert that the reset creates a distinct style alongside plain text. But if rendering fails, I should avoid that. I think I can assert that `(parsed.getColor(3) & Color.mask) == 0`, meaning checking if `-2147483648 & Color.mask` equals zero, which seems good.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Q97eRIX9uRWuvpORg70EwkLy|fc_023e2c15b1a448540169f87f1ce21481a0ba3cbbb5b95e81e6", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.lihaoyi/fansi_3/0.5.1/src/test/scala/com_lihaoyi/fansi_3/Fansi_3Test.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "    val parsed: Str = Str.Throw(\"A\\u001b[38;2;12;34;56mB\\u001b[48;2;1;2;3mC\\u001b[0mD\")\n    assertEquals(\"ABCD\", parsed.plainText)\n    assertEquals(0L, parsed.getColor(0))\n    assertEquals(Color.True(12, 34, 56).transform(0L), parsed.getColor(1))\n    assertEquals(Color.True(12, 34, 56).transform(0L), parsed.getColor(2) & Color.mask)\n    assertNotEquals(parsed.getColor(1), parsed.getColor(2))\n    assertEquals(0L, parsed.getColor(3))\n", "newText": "    val parsed: Str = Str.Throw(\"A\\u001b[38;2;12;34;56mB\\u001b[48;2;1;2;3mC\")\n    assertEquals(\"ABC\", parsed.plainText)\n    assertEquals(0L, parsed.getColor(0))\n    assertEquals(Color.True(12, 34, 56).transform(0L), parsed.getColor(1))\n    assertEquals(Color.True(12, 34, 56).transform(0L), parsed.getColor(2) & Color.mask)\n    assertEquals(Back.True(0x010203).transform(0L), parsed.getColor(2) & Back.mask)\n    assertNotEquals(parsed.getColor(1), parsed.getColor(2))\n\n    val resetParsed: Str = Str.Throw(\"A\\u001b[38;2;12;34;56mB\\u001b[0mC\")\n    assertEquals(\"ABC\", resetParsed.plainText)\n    assertEquals(0L, resetParsed.getColor(0))\n    assertEquals(Color.True(12, 34, 56).transform(0L), resetParsed.getColor(1))\n    assertEquals(0L, resetParsed.getColor(2))\n"}, {"oldText": "    val p